06/10/2010
BUCHAREST, Romania -- About 5,000 teachers and other employees in the education sector joined a protest Tuesday (October 5th) against austerity measures aimed at cutting the country's budget deficit.
They marched to the labour and education ministries, insisting on decent salaries, more investment in education and an end to job cuts.
They also demanded the government's resignation.
Another 1,500 demonstrators protested the austerity measures in the education field outside President Traian Basescu's office.
(AP, Mediafax - 05/10/10)
